moves.1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5: I have tried and failed countless times to defend against Fried Liver. This is my standard response now.
moves.6. Bb5+ c6 7. dxc6 bxc6 8. Bd3: I'm a huge fan of Qf3 here. Threatening Qxa1 if cxb5
moves.8... Ng4 9. Ne4 f5 10. Ng3: I think this is white's first mistake. Better imo would've been Nc3.
moves.10... Bc5: Attacking the f2 square twice forcing him to castle however...
moves.11. O-O Qh4: now I'm threatening mate. his only response can be h3
moves.12. h3 Nxf2 13. Qh5+: Huge mistake. Rxf2 Qxg3 is feel bad but necessary at this point.
moves.13... Qxh5 14. Nxh5 Nxd3+ 15. Kh1 Nxc1 1: 20 moves in and now he develops his knight?
